Business Brief -- Sotheby's Holdings Inc.:
   Fourth-Quarter Profit Fell
   By 33%, Revenue by 24%
Sotheby's stock was quoted at $15.125 a share, up 75
cents, in late New York Stock Exchange trading.
   The company was more upbeat about the future of its
primary auction business. "We approach 1992 with the belief
that the art auction market is more stable than it was a year
ago and that a gradual recovery is under way," said Michael
L. Ainslie, president and chief executive officer.